Name: Relief fragments with the name of Kha-em-wese
Description: These two fragments of a wall relief show a scene from a procession with gifts. The first two figures are Nile or fertility gods, who are easy to identify because of their very full forms. Behind them is a slender goddess. They all bear offering mats with loaves, birds in their nests and water plants. Underneath them are further plants, birds and fish. The vertical text on the right-hand side mentions Prince Kha-em-wese, a son of Ramesses II.
